snippet.textDisplay:
dude, why in the world would anyone have taken issue with the video the first time around?? I'm an over the top, protective dog mom like Jenna is for her dogs, and I did wonder about if it's comfortable for them, but it was clear in the video that she wondered the same thing and didn't have them in there for long. I thought the video was hilarious, and also really informative and interesting. I appreciate it, because dog things can be expensive as hell, and like Jenna I want the best for my dog. There's so many times I've bought her something that cost a lot of money but that just didn't work for her. That's totally normal if you care about your dog; you'll keep trying new things to see if they work, then pay attention to their cues to see if you should continue.


I think it's really good to have a loving, kind, compassionate and thoughtful person like Jenna doing a review like this because she WILL be objective, and for things like this, I might have been a bit curious about if I should be looking into something for my dog or not and this sort of video helps me know which way I roll. For my dog, I wouldn't have gotten her this most likely anyway because she's older and I think it would be bad on her spine, however I also have a thing she's clipped into every time we drive and I'm still scared she'll get injured in an accident. So that can be a genuine question to have to really consider -- in a regular car ride, a normal harness is way more comfortable; but in the event of an accident, what is the safest thing for my dog? That's the sort of question that would drive someone to check into something like this, and that's the sort of question a loving, GOOD dog mom would ask.


Anyone coming for Jenna over this just wants to have something to be angry about and isn't taking any context whatsoever into account, nor are they trying in any form to be objective. They've simply gone into it deciding ahead of time what their mood will be, and it doesn't matter what reality says; they'll make things up if they need to in order to do the mental gymnastics to end up where they decided from the start they wanted to be.


Jeez. The internet and people are sometimes just severely unhappy and need to take a step back, breathe, and recenter themselves to assess their actions and words.


Jenna, it's so stupid you had to add that disclaimer, and I'm sorry you had to - your initial video was extremely clear, it's just people who felt like not listening for whatever reason. Maybe they were in a bad place at the time and they projected onto you, I don't know. But it goes to show, once more, how responsible and caring you are that you did add this disclaimer, an act which in my opinion even further refutes any silly assumptions or accusations in the first place.
